# Prompt Tuning Gemma-2 9B for English → Persian Translation
# Project Overview
This project explores parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) using Prompt Tuning on a large language model (Gemma-2 9B Instruct) for the task of English → Persian machine translation.
Instead of fine-tuning all model weights, this approach learns a small set of trainable virtual prompt tokens, making it:
•	memory efficient
•	fast to train
•	suitable for low-resource settings
________________________________________
 Objective
•	Evaluate baseline translation performance of Gemma-2 9B
•	Apply Prompt Tuning (PEFT method)
•	Train on a small parallel dataset (10 sentence pairs)
•	Measure improvement using BLEU score
•	Analyze effect of lightweight adaptation on translation quality
________________________________________
 Model Used
🔹 Gemma-2 9B Instruct
•	Large instruction-tuned causal language model
•	Loaded in 4-bit quantized mode (BitsAndBytes)
•	Supports efficient inference on limited hardware
________________________________________
 Dataset
A small custom parallel dataset:
•	10 English sentences
•	10 Persian translations
Used for:
•	Prompt tuning training
•	Evaluation before and after adaptation
•	BLEU score computation
________________________________________
 Methodology
🔹 1. Baseline Evaluation
•	Model used without any adaptation
•	Translation performed using prompt:
Translate the following sentence to Persian:
{sentence}
Translation:
•	BLEU score computed using SacreBLEU
________________________________________
🔹 2. Prompt Tuning (PEFT)
Instead of updating full model weights:
•	Introduced 20 virtual tokens
•	Only prompt embeddings were trained
•	Model parameters were frozen
Configuration:
•	Task: Causal Language Modeling
•	Virtual tokens: 20
•	Token dimension: model hidden size
•	Optimizer: AdamW (lr = 1e-3)
________________________________________
🔹 3. Training Strategy
•	Micro-batch training on 10 sentence pairs
•	5 training epochs
•	Loss computed using token-level supervision
•	Gradient updates applied only to prompt tokens
________________________________________
🔹 4. Evaluation Metric
•	BLEU score (SacreBLEU)
•	Comparison:
o	Before Prompt Tuning
o	After Prompt Tuning
________________________________________
 Results
Model Stage	BLEU Score
Before tuning	~2.83
After tuning	~5.10
Improvement	+2.27
________________________________________
 Key Findings
•	Even with very small dataset (10 samples), prompt tuning improves performance
•	Virtual tokens help guide model behavior without full fine-tuning
•	Gemma-2 9B can adapt to translation tasks using minimal updates
•	BLEU improvement confirms effectiveness of PEFT approach
________________________________________

Tech Stack
•	Python
•	PyTorch
•	Hugging Face Transformers
•	PEFT (Prompt Tuning)
•	BitsAndBytes (4-bit quantization)
•	SacreBLEU
________________________________________
 Conclusion
This project demonstrates how Prompt Tuning (PEFT) can efficiently adapt large language models like Gemma-2 9B to a new task (English → Persian translation) using minimal computational resources.
Despite using a very small dataset, the method shows measurable improvement, highlighting the potential of parameter-efficient learning for low-resource NLP tasks.

